3-24:A key notion governing the formation of hypotheses is that of consistency, defined below: Definition 2 (Consistency) .
3-25:We say that: • An agent is consistent (Cons(ai)) iff Cons(hi, Oi) (that is, its hypothesis is consistent with its observation set) .
3-26:• An agent ai consistent with a partner agent aj iff Cons(ai) and Cons(hi, Oj) (that is, this agent is consistent and its hypothesis can explain the observation set of the other agent) .
