6-36:Effectiveness of a protocol The proportion of agents surviving the fire over the initial number of agents involved in the experiment will determine the effectiveness of a given protocol .
6-37:If this value is high, the protocol has been effective to propagate the information and or for the agents to refine their hypotheses and determine the best way to the exit .
6-38:Efficiency of a protocol Typically, the use of supporting information will involve a communication overhead .
6-39:We will assume here that the efficiency of a given protocol is characterised by the data flow induced by this protocol .
